The World Bank said it approved a97.4 mln dlr loan for China to help boost fertilizer output inorder to increase agricultural production.    The 20-year loan supports a project aimed at improving theefficiency of medium-scale fertilizer plants through technicalrenovations and energy conservation, the bank said.    It said the project also seeks to reduce agriculturalnutrient imbalances by building the capacity for phosphatefertilizer production and to improve institutional efficiencyby introducing modern economic, financial and operationalsystems and techniques. Reuter&#3;